The present works are unable to treat water to modern standards and one new works at{Blackmoorfoot}will replace the existing three.
When the rain falls it is usally clean but by the time it gets to the reservoir it has got clay,mud,twigs, leaves and grass as well as germs in it,so it has to go to the{Treatment {Plant.}
First chemicals are added to make the lumps of dirt stick together.Then tiny bubbles of air are blown in to make the dirt float to the top.The water flows down sand pipes.Dirt sticks to the sand,after that chlorine is added to kill the germs.{The water is then {pumped into a service reservoir {waiting for the consumer to turn on {her tap.
